entralization, and delegation reforms. These changes have in turn changed the role of national and subnational levels of government, as well as nongovernmental actors, in the organization, management, and provision of labor market policies and services. López-Santana's multidisciplinary, comparative, and multilevel approach to welfare state change is an original and important step forward in our understanding of welfare reforms enacted since the mid-1990s.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aDecentralization in governmentxEuropean Union countriesxEuropexEuropean Union countriesxUnited States. 0aDecentralization in governmentxUnited States. 0aDecentralization in governmentzEuropean Union countries. 0aDecentralization in governmentzUnited States. 0aPublic welfare administrationxEuropean Union countries. 0aPublic welfare administrationxUnited States. 0aPublic welfare administrationzEuropean Union countries. 0aPublic welfare administrationzUnited States. 0aPublic welfarexEuropean Union countries. 0aPublic welfarexUnited States. 0aPublic welfarezEuropean Union countries. 0aPublic welfarezUnited States. 0aWelfare statexEuropean Union countries. 0aWelfare statexUnited States. 0aWelfare statezEuropean Union countries. 0aWelfare statezUnited States. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Economy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 4aPublic Policy : Public Policy. 4aSociology : Sociology of Work. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Comparative Politics.2bisacsh1 aBüchs, Milena, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2015z978311149061840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438454696423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438454696/original  a978-3-11-149061-8  SUNY Pr